#: i18n.program_bonus_help
msgid   "Ignore pattern is a regular expression which is used to filter out "
        "stuff using their name.\r\n"
        "If -B is used, entities with ~ or .bak suffix will be ignored.\r\n"
        "If -a is NOT used, entities with . (a literal dot) prefix will be "
        "ignored.\r\n"
        "By default, the ignore pattern is case-INsensitive. Currently you "
        "can't change that\r\n"
        "\r\n"
        "Comments and line breaks are allowed like this:\r\n"
        "( # this is a comment\r\n"
        "abc\r\n"
        "def\r\n"
        ") # done \r\n"
        "\r\n"
        "DIR_PRESET environment variable points to the preset that dir will "
        "use (gnu, win, ccd).\r\n"
        "Check dir(5) manual page for more informations."
msgstr  ""

